## Security Manifesto

Beach Concierge implements **Defense in Depth** across six independent layers. Bypassing any single layer still leaves five active.

### Layer 1 — HTTP Security Headers

Set at the Vite dev-server and preview levels via `vite.config.ts`. **Must be mirrored at the nginx/Cloudflare level for production** (see production checklist below).

| Header | Value | Threat Mitigated |
|--------|-------|-----------------|
| `X-Frame-Options` | `DENY` | Clickjacking |
| `X-Content-Type-Options` | `nosniff` | MIME-type confusion attacks |
| `Referrer-Policy` | `strict-origin-when-cross-origin` | URL parameter leakage |
| `Permissions-Policy` | `payment=(), usb=()` | Rogue API access in injected scripts |
| `Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy` | `same-origin` | Cross-origin window.opener attacks |
| `Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy` | `same-origin` | Cross-origin resource reads |

> **Note on Helmet.js:** Helmet.js is an Express middleware library — it is not applicable to a static SPA. The headers above are the direct equivalent and are enforced by the Vite dev server and will be enforced by nginx/Cloudflare in production.

### Layer 2 — Content Security Policy (CSP)

A strict CSP `<meta>` tag in `index.html` with `default-src 'none'` and explicit per-type allowlists:

```
default-src 'none'                    ← Block everything by default
script-src  'self' unpkg.com youtube.com accounts.google.com
style-src   'self' fonts.googleapis.com unpkg.com
img-src     'self' data: blob: *.openstreetmap.org i.postimg.cc ...
connect-src 'self' api.open-meteo.com nominatim.openstreetmap.org ...
frame-src   youtube.com                ← ONLY YouTube embeds
object-src  'none'                     ← Flash/plugins: permanently disabled
upgrade-insecure-requests              ← Force HTTPS on all sub-resources
```

**Proven in production:** The CSP actively blocked a `wallpaperflare.com` image during development before the domain was added to `img-src` — demonstrating the policy is live and enforced, not theoretical.

### Layer 3 — Subresource Integrity (SRI)

Leaflet CSS (the only external stylesheet) is loaded with a `sha384` hash:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet"
  href="https://unpkg.com/leaflet@1.9.4/dist/leaflet.css"
  integrity="sha384-sHL9NAb7lN7rfvG5lfHpm643Xkcjzp4jFvuavGOndn6pjVqS6ny56CAt3nsEVT4H"
  crossorigin="anonymous" />
```

A supply-chain attack against `unpkg.com` that modifies the CSS will cause the browser to **refuse to load the file entirely**.

### Layer 4 — XSS Prevention (Multi-point Sanitization)

```js
// sanitize() applied at every innerHTML insertion point
function sanitize(value) {
  return String(value)
    .replace(/&/g, '&amp;').replace(/</g, '&lt;')
    .replace(/>/g, '&gt;').replace(/"/g, '&quot;')
    .replace(/'/g, '&#x27;');
}
```

| Insertion Point | Risk Without Sanitization |
|----------------|--------------------------|
| Social feed messages | Stored XSS via localStorage |
| Game card (user name) | Reflected XSS |
| Grid ID in HTML | HTML injection via URL parameter |
| Chat messages | Stored XSS — uses `textContent`, immune by construction |

### Layer 5 — Input Validation & Rate Limiting

**Sliding-window rate limiters** (four independent instances):

| Limiter | Limit | Window | Protects |
|---------|-------|--------|----------|
| `_signupLimiter` | 3 calls | 60 s | Signup form spam |
| `_chatLimiter` | 10 calls | 30 s | Concierge chat flooding |
| `_socialLimiter` | 10 calls | 60 s | Social feed spam |
| `_noiseLimiter` | 6 calls | 60 s | Noise sensor manipulation |

**Input hardening by field:**

| Field | Validation |
|-------|-----------|
| Name | 100-char cap + control-char strip (`\x00–\x1F`, `\x7F`) |
| Phone | E.164 digit count (7–15) |
| Chat message | 500-char cap |
| Grid ID | Regex `^BEACH-[A-Z]{1,2}\d{1,2}$` before any localStorage key use |
| Noise dB | Physical range guard: 20–140 dB |

### Layer 6 — SecurityLogger (PII-Safe Audit Trail)

```js
// NEVER logs user-supplied values — only action type + reason code + timestamp
SecurityLogger.rateLimitExceeded('chat-send', 10, 30_000);
// → [BeachConcierge:Security] RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED { action: "chat-send", ... }
```

Four event types: `rateLimitExceeded`, `validationFailure`, `storageAnomaly`, `checkpoint`.  
All emit structured JSON with a `[BeachConcierge:Security]` prefix — ready for **Cloudflare Logpush → Datadog/Splunk** in Phase 2 without any code change.

