### Running Tests

```bash
# Single run (CI mode)
pnpm --filter @workspace/simple-website run test

# Watch mode (development)
pnpm --filter @workspace/simple-website run test:watch

# With coverage report
pnpm --filter @workspace/simple-website run test:coverage
```

### Design Philosophy

**Testability by design:** All business logic that can be executed without a DOM is extracted into `src/core.js` as pure, side-effect-free exports. The rate limiter factory accepts an injectable `clock` function — making time-dependent tests fully deterministic without mocking `Date.now()` globally.

```js
// Deterministic rate-limiter test — no global mocks needed
let time = 0;
const limiter = createRateLimiter(3, 60_000, () => time);
limiter.check('signup'); // allowed
limiter.check('signup'); // allowed
limiter.check('signup'); // allowed
expect(limiter.check('signup')).toBe(false); // blocked

time = 61_000; // advance the clock
expect(limiter.check('signup')).toBe(true);  // window has slid
```

