## CI/CD Pipeline

Three jobs run on every push and pull request:

```
push / PR
    │
    ├── Job 1: typecheck    ── tsc --noEmit across all workspace packages
    │
    ├── Job 2: unit-tests   ── Vitest (88 tests) + coverage upload
    │
    └── Job 3: build-check  ── Vite production bundle verification
              (runs only after jobs 1 & 2 pass)
```

**Coverage artifacts** are uploaded to GitHub Actions on every run (14-day retention). The build job stubs `PORT` and `BASE_PATH` environment variables that the Vite config requires, ensuring the production bundle can always be verified in CI.

### Adding the workflow to GitHub

The workflow file is at `.github/workflows/ci.yml`. It activates automatically once pushed to GitHub. Update the badge URL in this README by replacing `<your-org>` with your GitHub organisation or username.

