## Phase 1 Roadmap — Backend Migration

The current architecture deliberately defers backend infrastructure to maximise development velocity and eliminate operational complexity during the MVP phase. The following table maps each remaining security and scalability requirement to its Phase 1 implementation:

| Requirement | Current State | Phase 1 Implementation |
|-------------|---------------|----------------------|
| **Authentication** | None | Clerk (OpenID Connect, PKCE) |
| **HttpOnly cookies** | N/A (no session) | Express `cookie-parser` + `SameSite=Strict; HttpOnly; Secure` |
| **CSRF protection** | CSP `form-action 'self'` | Clerk CSRF tokens + `SameSite=Strict` |
| **Helmet.js** | Vite header equivalents | Express + `helmet()` middleware |
| **Server-side rate limiting** | Client-side sliding window | Redis (`ioredis`) + `express-rate-limit` |
| **HSTS** | Client can't set this | nginx `Strict-Transport-Security` header |
| **CSP nonces** | `'unsafe-inline'` for styles | Per-request nonces, removes `unsafe-inline` |
| **Order persistence** | None | PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM |
| **Real-time courier** | Simulated | WebSocket / Server-Sent Events |
| **Security monitoring** | `console.warn` events | Cloudflare Logpush → Datadog SIEM |

### Phase 1 Architecture Target

```
                    Cloudflare (DDoS, WAF, HSTS, rate limit tier 1)
                            │
                    nginx (security headers, TLS termination)
                            │
              ┌─────────────┴──────────────┐
              │                            │
         Static CDN                  Express API
         (current SPA)               (new in Phase 1)
                                          │
                                    ┌─────┴──────┐
                                   Clerk       Redis
                                  (auth)   (rate limits,
                                            session cache)
                                          │
                                      PostgreSQL
                                     (Drizzle ORM)
```

