## Architecture Decisions

- **No framework by design:** The entire app is vanilla JS in one script.js — chosen for zero dependency surface, instant cold-start, and minimal XSS attack surface.
- **Defense-in-Depth:** 6 independent security layers (CSP, SRI, sanitize, rate limiters, SecurityLogger, HTTP headers) so bypassing one still leaves 5 active.
- **O(1) product lookups:** `_productById` (Map) and `_categoryById` (Map) built once at startup; all cart/checkout/history code uses them instead of `Array.find()`.
- **RAF + rIC batching:** `updateCartBar` is RAF-batched; `renderBundles`, `renderOrderHistory`, `renderPointsUI` run via `requestIdleCallback` — heavy DOM work never blocks user input.
- **Memoized pricing:** `getItemPrice` uses `_priceCache` (Map) so variant price lookups are O(1) on repeat calls within a session.

## Security Architecture (v2.2.0)

### Layer 1 — HTTP Security Headers (Vite dev + production)
Set in `vite.config.ts` `server.headers` and `preview.headers`:
- `X-Frame-Options: DENY` — clickjacking prevention
- `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff` — MIME-sniffing prevention
- `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`
- `Permissions-Policy: camera=(self), microphone=(self), geolocation=(self), payment=(), usb=()`
- `Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin`
- `Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin`

**Production (nginx/Cloudflare — required pre-launch):**
```nginx
add_header X-Frame-Options "DENY" always;
add_header Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains" always;
```

### Layer 2 — Content Security Policy (CSP meta tag)
Full CSP in `index.html` with `default-src 'none'`, explicit allowlists per content type, `upgrade-insecure-requests`, `frame-src youtube.com` only. Proven live — blocked wallpaperflare.com before domain was added to allowlist.

### Layer 3 — Subresource Integrity (SRI)
Leaflet CSS loaded with `integrity="sha384-sHL9NAb7lN7rfvG5lfHpm643Xkcjzp4jFvuavGOndn6pjVqS6ny56CAt3nsEVT4H"`. Tampered CDN response = browser refuses to load.

### Layer 4 — XSS Prevention
`sanitize()` applied at all 5 innerHTML insertion points. Chat messages use `textContent` (cannot inject HTML by design). `isValidGridId()` regex guard before any localStorage key construction.

### Layer 5 — Input Validation + Rate Limiting
4 sliding-window rate limiters: signup (3/60s), chat (10/30s), social (10/60s), noise (6/60s). Name field strips control chars + 100-char cap. Noise input guarded to physical range 20–140 dB.

### Layer 6 — SecurityLogger (PII-free)
4 event types: `rateLimitExceeded`, `validationFailure`, `storageAnomaly`, `checkpoint`. All emit structured `[BeachConcierge:Security]` prefixed JSON — ready for Cloudflare Logpush → Datadog/Splunk in Phase 2.

