         *
         * Why client-side rate limiting?
         *   Client-side limits do not replace server-side limits (which are the
         *   authoritative enforcement layer). They serve two purposes:
         *   1. UX: immediate feedback to a frustrated user double-tapping submit.
         *   2. Telemetry: SecurityLogger.rateLimitExceeded fires, creating an
         *      observable signal that can be collected in Phase 2 via a beacon.
         *
         * @param {number} maxAttempts - Max calls allowed within the window.
         * @param {number} windowMs    - Rolling window duration in milliseconds.
         * @returns {{ check(action: string): boolean, reset(action: string): void }}
         */
        function _createRateLimiter(maxAttempts, windowMs) {
            /** @type {Map<string, number[]>} action → sorted array of call timestamps */
